# Publish on every change (GitHub Pages)

This repo deploys via **GitHub Actions** on **push to `main`** (`.github/workflows/deploy-github-pages.yml`). The live site only updates after a successful push.

When you change **source, assets, or workflow/config** and the user has not asked to skip version control:

1. **Commit** with a short, clear message.
2. **Push** to `origin` on the current branch (usually `main`).

Treat “done” as **committed and pushed**, not only edited locally. If there is nothing to commit, do not push. If push fails (auth, conflicts), say what failed and how to fix it.

When you ship **user-visible** changes, bump `src/app/version.ts` (`APP_VERSION`) and state that string in your reply so the user can match it to the tiny top-left label after refresh.

Do not assume the user will run git commands later unless they explicitly asked to keep changes local.
